                    <note>
                        <date type="foundation" notBefore="0200" notAfter="1500"/>
                        <ab type="history">Dabr.</ab>
                        <ab type="tabot">
                            <measure quantity="3">3</measure>  3 tābots,                                
                                  <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Mary</persName>,  
                            <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9684Uriel">ʿUrāʾel</persName>,
                            <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1284Abrehaa">Abrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa</persName>.                                                               
                        </ab>
                                                <ab type="description">The church of St Mary Zion stands on the foundation dating at least to the Aksumite time, 
                            other remains of Aksumite stonework are visible in the church compound.
                            An old rock-hewn church is located nearby, called by the local people <foreign xml:lang="ti">Naḵwāl ʾƎmni</foreign>.
                            An archeological site has been recently set up just outside the church compound, where the community 
                            started digging earth in order to build a new church, but stopped when bones and remains of pottery were found. 
                            The time of the foundation of the church is not known. 
                            Six manuscripts were inventarized on <date>17 November 2023</date> . 
                            An unknown number of manuscripts remained unrecorded.</ab>
                    </note>
